Caution: Use caution in patients with impaired liver and kidney function. Not recommended for use in children < 2 years, except for doctor's instructions. Do not exceed the recommended dose. Contra Indication: Hypersensitivity, heart problems, diabetes mellitus, severe liver dysfunction

Ingredients: Paracetamol 120 mg, Pseudoephedrine HCl 7.5 mg, Gliseril guaiakoalat 25 mg, Chlorpheniramine Maleate 0.5 mg
Caution: Use of Termorex Plus must be stopped at the first signs of an allergic reaction such as rash, itching, sore throat, fever, arthralgia, pallor, or other signs. This drug should be used with caution in patients who have asthma
Side Effect: Drowsiness, stomach-intestinal disorders, insomnia (difficulty sleeping), restlessness/anxiety, excitement, trembling, tachycardia, ventricular arrhythmia, dry mouth, fast heartbeat, difficulty urinating
Contra Indication: Patients who have sensitivity to other sympathomimetic drugs such as ephedrine, phenylephrine. Patients who are using monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitors, because they can increase blood pressure. Patients suffering from diabetes mellitus, heart disease, severe hypertension, severe coronary artery disease, prostatic hypertrophy, hyperthyroidism, and closed angle galucoma.
